This paper is primarily focused on evaluating the robustness of image classifiers, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses ways to enhance the robustness of these classifiers, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for adversarial attacks, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
